<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Remarks.</emphasis>
Three subspecies were recorded from the 
<collectingCountry box="[799,1006,151,176]" name="Philippines" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Philippine Islands</collectingCountry>
: 
<emphasis box="[1018,1161,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P. t. leopoldi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, J." box="[1170,1342,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11349" refString="Bequaert, J. (1934) Les races de coloration de Vespa luctuosa de Saussure et de Polistes tenebricosus Lepeletier. Bulletin du Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique, Series 28, 10, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1934">Bequaert, 1934</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[1359,1428,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[178,1404,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[178,1404,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Polistes (Gyrostoma) tenebricosus Lepeletier, 1836. 7, 11, ♀. 8–10, ♂. 7, subspecies leopoldi Bequaert, 1940. 8–11, typical form. 7, Habitus. 8, Head in frontal view. 9, Head in lateral view. 10, Apex of antenna in lateral view. 11, Propodeum in postero-dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614893/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) from Negros, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bequaert, 1940" authorityName="Bequaert" authorityYear="1940" box="[308,691,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="tenebricosus" subSpecies="nigrosericans">
<emphasis box="[308,512,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P. t. nigrosericans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, J." box="[519,691,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" pagination="265 - 272" refId="ref11389" refString="Bequaert, J. (1940) Notes on Oriental Polistes wasps (Hymenoptera: Vespidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 66, 265 - 272." type="journal article" year="1940">Bequaert, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Luzon, and 
<emphasis box="[895,1088,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P. t. sibuyanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, J." box="[1096,1268,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" pagination="265 - 272" refId="ref11389" refString="Bequaert, J. (1940) Notes on Oriental Polistes wasps (Hymenoptera: Vespidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 66, 265 - 272." type="journal article" year="1940">Bequaert, 1940</bibRefCitation>
from Sibuyan. The subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bequaert" authorityYear="1940" box="[338,550,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="tenebricosus" subSpecies="nigrosericans">
<emphasis box="[338,550,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P. t. nigrosericans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is elevated to species rank above, while the taxonomic status of the other subspecies remains unclear due to the absence of male specimens to be examined. Three females of subspecies 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P. t. leopoldi</emphasis>
were examined and they show characters similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bequaert" authorityYear="1940" box="[847,1081,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrosericans" subGenus="Gyrostoma">
<emphasis box="[847,866,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[886,907,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">G.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[928,1081,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">nigrosericans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but without examining males, the status of this subspecies cannot be clarified. Specimens of subspecies 
<emphasis box="[975,1167,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">P. t. sibuyanensis</emphasis>
were not available.
</paragraph>
